<problem id="fs-id1167133659256">
<para id="fs-id1167133334295">A point source of light is 50 cm in front of a converging lens of focal length 30 cm. A concave mirror with a focal length of 20 cm is placed 25 cm behind the lens. Where does the final image form, and what are its orientation and magnification?</para>
